   But the Aroner measure is certain to provide some of the most
intense debate and wrenching political decisions of the session.
</P>
<P>
   Carol Hogan, a lobbyist for the California Catholic Conference,
which represents the state's bishops, said her organization would
fight Aroner's bill vigorously.
</P>
<P>
   ``Compassion means to `suffer with,' '' Hogan said. ``It's
easier to offer someone relief, which may mean relief from looking
at them suffer.''
</P>
<P>
   Hogan also said terminally ill patients concerned about high
medical costs might choose to take the fatal doses. ``It's a whole
lot cheaper for someone to kill themselves than to ask their HMO to
care for them for another six months,'' she said.
</P>
<P>
   But a study published in the New England Journal of Medicine
last month reported that none of the 23 people in Oregon who
