   &UR; WASHINGTON (w) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   OLIPHANT-COLUMN (Washington) _ Karl Malden himself may give the
Oscar speech for Elia Kazan. One hopes the applause is perfunctory,
for this is a dishonorable man. By Thomas Oliphant. &UR;  &LR; (w and k
coding.)
