   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   HILLARY-SENATE (New York) _ It's clear that Hillary Clinton has
opinions, new and old, that could be used for and against her in a
campaign. And it's clear that, long after her husband, she has made
her own migration from left to left of center. By Fred Kaplan. 1620
words.
</P>
<P>
   MA-BIG-SCORE (Malden, Mass.) _ John ``Trixi'' Trischitta was the
water boy on the football team; Martin Robbins was one of the
team's heroes. They went their own ways, fell on hard times, but
came together in what investigators say is a scheme to steal
millions. By David Armstrong. (2 takes)
</P>
<P>
   SAILOR-SHIP (Boston) _ A former seaman apprentice and the
retired warship USS Massachusetts -- thrown together by fate for
the battleship's maiden voyage -- to reunite after the ship's
refurbishing is complete. By Thomas Farragher. 770 words. PHOTO
</P>
<P>
   &UR; COMMENTARY (k) &LR;
</P>
<P>
