<P>
   A pot of gumbo attracts like a magnet. It pulls you to smell the
smokiness of the dark brown roux, to dip in a spoon and bite into a
succulent chunk of sausage or a tender shrimp, to sip the hearty
broth and feel the tickle of pepper at the back of the throat.
