   BKN-ROCKETS (Houston) _ In a battle of two struggling Midwest
Division rivals, the Houston Rockets play host to the San Antonio
Spurs at the Compaq Center here. By MICHAEL MURPHY.
</P>
<P>
   BKC-DREXLER (New Orleans) _ It has been a roller-coaster of an
inaugural season for University of Houston basketball coach Clyde
Drexler, who now guides his young Cougars into the Conference USA
postseason tournament starting Wednesday. By JERRY WIZIG.
</P>
<P>
   BBN-ASTROS (Kissimmee, Fla.) _ Rus Johnson has shown that he is
ready to play in the major leagues, yet he remains on the outside
looking in as the Houston Astros head into the 1999 season.
Johnson, who has enjoyed a taste of major-league success the past
two seasons only to be sent back down, is now learning to play
shortstop in an effort to get back to ``The Show.'' By CARLTON
THOMPSON.
