   THE LAYOUT'S DONE FOR YOU: Stories marked as a CoxNet layout are
available for purchase in paginated form:
www.nytsyn.com/pageexpress.
</P>
<P>
   BARBIE-BEAUTY - Venus, Helen, Cleopatria, Catherine Denueuve,
Barbie. A learned man opines on legendary beauty and where Barbie
fits in. (Browning, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   BARBIE-SIDE - Sidebar about ancient Roman doll found in 1889.
(Browning, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   DONT-TALK - Talk, talk and talk some more. That's the advice
relationship ``experts'' have long given couples with problems.
Well, forget it. A long-term study by two universities found that
couples with great communications skills aren't necessarily any
happier. The smart communicators simply insulted each other more
effectively. (Reed, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   ENTERTAINMENT/ARTS
</P>
<P>
   FASHION-MILAN _ Scott Walton reports from the fashion runways in
Milan. (Walton, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   MUSIC-FESTIVAL _ AUSTIN, Texas _ The music industry calls it
``spring break,'' as its swarms invade the streets of Austin,
Texas, with the margarita-swilling abandon of collegians in
Daytona, Fla. For the Austin economy, it is ``Christmas in March,''
though local hotels, clubs and restaurants consider it more like
Mardi Gras and the Super Bowl rolled into one. It is best
recognized by the unpronounceable acronym of SXSW, though it is
more properly known as the South by Southwest Music and Media
Conference (by day, and the South by Southwest Music Festival by
night). Whatever one calls it, SXSW will mark its 13th year with
this year's run. From March 17-21, it will present more than 600
musical acts at 37 clubs and other facilities throughout the city.
It expects to draw some 6,000 conference registrants from across
the country and around the world. (McLeese, Austin
American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   TV-VANZANT _ Iyanla Vanzant, spiritual guru, is a regular on
TV's ``Oprah.'' Her daily affirmations are featured in a line of
Hallmark cards. And her string of bestsellers includes ``Acts of
Faith,'' a book that's been called ``the black women's Bible.'' She
is one of the few African-Americans in the crowded and profitable
field of spiritual guides who have made careers counseling the
masses on everything from finding their inner child to preparing
for the afterlife. Over the last three years, Vanzant _ whose first
name means ``great mother'' in the Nigerian culture known as Yoruba
_ has also become an icon for many black women who see her as a
reflection of who they are, and who they can become. (Harris,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution) EDS: Photos available. MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   TVSURFER-COLUMN _ ATLANTA _ On the last night of sweeps, Barbara
Walters airs her interview with Monica Lewinsky in a two-hour
``20/20.'' Plus CBS has ``Shania Twain's Winter Break.'' (Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   MONICA-WEB _ ABC will not be able to post the transcripts or
video of the Barbara Walters interview with Monica Lewinsky because
she gave the network only the U.S. rights to it. She and her family
are selling rights to the interview abroad for hundreds of
thousands of dollars. ABC, meanwhile, can only use one of its
outlets to disseminate the story.. (Katz, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   MONICA-WALTERS - Getting ready for the Monica Lewinsky interview
with Barbara Walters. What to look for. (Houck, Palm Beach Post).
8.
</P>
<P>
   SCIENCE/MEDICINE
</P>
<P>
   HEALTH-BRIEFS _ A compilation of health briefs from the past
week. (Cox News Service) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   CDC-GUJLFWAR _ Checking whether anything to report out of CDC's
conference on Gulf War syndrome. Conference is to discuss ways to
set up studies to once and for all satisfy veterans groups as to
whether any links exist between reported illnesses and chemicals
vets may have been exposed to. (Guthrie, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
