<P>
   OLY-GA-FUNDRAISING _ Billy Payne established the public-sounding
Georgia Amateur Athletics Foundation as a body to handle
fundraising for the Atlanta Olympics. Not much has been heard of
the GAAF, aside from small grants it hands out to local sports
groups, until the recent flap over ACOG records. They belong to the
GAAF, which refuses to release them to the public until they are
catalogued. A look at the GAAF. (Turner/Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
