   BUSH-ANALYSIS (Washington) _ The Bush and Dole names are nothing
new to Republican presidential primaries. We look at the cool
relationship between these two establishment families and how the
party would fare with the son, Texas Gov. George W. Bush, and the
wife, Elizabeth Dole, on the 2000 campaign trail. By CRAGG HINES.
(Already filed.)
</P>
<P>
   NATIONAL NEWS (``a'' category)
</P>
<P>
   BUSH-2000 (Austin, Texas) _ Facing mounting national pressure
from Republicans to run seek the presidency next year, Texas Gov.
George W. Bush announces he is forming a campaign committee that
will raise money and pave the way for a campaign. But Bush, 52,
continues to say he will make no decision about a campaign until
later this year. By LAURA TOLLEY. (Already filed.)
</P>
<P>
   BUSH-LEGLISLATURE (Austin, Texas) _ Gov. George W. Bush stops
being coy and puts his presidential campaign in gear. Some people
are wondering if he can do the same with his legislative program.
Seven weeks into the legislative session, only one of Bush's
priorities _ a tax break for small oil and gas producers _ is
anywhere close to becoming law, and it may still spark a fight. By
CLAY ROBISON. (Already filed.)
</P>
<P>
   PAROLE-TEXAS (Austin, Texas) _ Texas' senior parole official
urges the state Legislature not to require open-door clemency
hearings for murderers facing the death penalty. By JOHN GONZALEZ.
(Already filed._
</P>
