<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Federated report more positive than expected
 &HT;    By Jim Bohman
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   DAYTON, Ohio _ Federated Department Stores Inc., operator of
Lazarus, Bloomingdale's, Macy's and other department store chains,
surprised analysts by reporting that fiscal 1998 net income jumped
19 percent before extraordinary charges.
</P>
<P>
   The Cincinnati-based chain of more than 400 department stores in
33 states reported fully diluted net income per share of $3.06,
before charges, topping expectations of retailing analysts by four
cents per share.
</P>
<P>
   In the fourth quarter, Federated earned $1.88 per share, beating
consensus expectations of $1.82 per share.
</P>
<P>
   ``This past year was a very good one for Federated,'' said James
M. Zimmerman, chairman and chief executive, of the year's results.
``We were particularly pleased with our very strong performance in
the important fourth quarter, including both sales and gross
margin.''
</P>
<P>
   For fiscal 1998, Federated posted earnings of $685 million,
excluding an extraordinary charge related to early retirement of
debt. This compares with earnings of $575 million for the previous
fiscal year, which had unusual charges for debt retirement.
</P>
<P>
   Diluted earnings per share rose to $3.06 for fiscal 1998, versus
$2.58 for fiscal 1997, a gain of 19 percent.
</P>
<P>
   In the fourth quarter, net income was $408 million or $1.88 per
share, compared with $379 million, or $1.66 a share, in fiscal
1997.
</P>
<P>
   Sales last year totaled $15.8 billion, up 1.1 percent. On a
comparable store basis, 52-week sales increased 2.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
   In the fourth quarter, sales totaled $5.2 billion, up 2.9
percent over the previous year's fourth quarter. On a comparable
store basis, fourth quarter sales rose 4.1 percent compared with
fiscal 1997
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By The DAYTON NEWSPAPERS INC., DAYTON, OHIO
</P>
<P>
   AP-NY-03-02-99 2046E
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
