This advertisement started appearing last week in newspapers at the
nation's Ivy League colleges. Already, more than 200 women have
responded to what is believed to be the largest amount of money
offered for a woman's eggs. The sponsors have chosen to remain
anonymous, according to Darlene Pinkerton, who with her
lawyer-husband, Thomas Pinkerton, placed the advertisement on
behalf of an infertile couple. (New York Times Photo)
