(Cynthia Howe/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT22) MADISON, Wisc. -- March 02, 1999 --
COLLEGE-SUPERVISION-2, 3-02 -- Writing instructor Nelson Graff,
right, talks with Vinai Gondi, of Milwaukee, during a tutoring
session after dinner near the cafeteria at Chadbourne Hall at the
University of Wisconsin on Monday. Three decades after American
college students defiantly threw off the vestiges of curfews, dress
codes and dormitory house mothers, a revolution is under way in
undergraduate life that may be quieter but no less
significant.(Andy Manis/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT21) ST. LOUIS, Mo. -- March 02, 1999 -- MONSANTO-DUPONT,
3-02 -- Robert B. Shapiro, the chief executive of the Monsanto Co.,
in his St. Louis office. He and other executives are in merger
negotiations with DuPont, a much larger company with more
traditional ways. The result has been a peculiar courtship, with
Shapiro trying to allow Monsanto to retain its special character
and habits. (Bill Stover/New York Times Photo) *LITE
</P>
<P>
   (NYT20) MADISON, Wisc. -- March 02, 1999 -- COLLEGE-SUPERVISION,
