<P>
   (NYT19) CARLOTTA, Calif -- March 02, 1998 -- FOREST-ACCORD, 3-02
-- Part of the Headwaters Forest looking northwest near Carlotta in
November, 1998. The grove of majestic redwoods, some as tall as
20-story buildings and more than 2,000 years old, has been saved by
a late-night deal between the government and Pacific Lumber which
owns the tract on the blustery, fog-shrouded California Coast.
(Kent Porter/Santa Rosa Press Democrat) *LITE
</P>
<P>
   (NYT18) WASHINGTON -- March 02, 1999 -- COUNSEL-LAW, 3-02 --
Deputy Attorney General Eric Holder, right, talks Rep. George
Gekas, R-Pa., chairman of the House Subcommittee on Commercial and
Administrative Law, prior to testifying on the independent counsel
law on Tuesday. The Clinton administration withdrew its support for
the law saying the Watergate-inspired investigations statute ``has
failed in its goal of removing politics from the process.'' Gekas
was one of the impeachment managers in the Senate trial of
President Clinton. A portrait of Rep. Henry Hyde, R-Ill., chairman
of the House Judiciary Committee, hangs above. Hyde led the House
impeachment managers in the trial. (Paul Hosefros/New York Times
Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT17) TEMPE, Ariz. -- March 02, 1999 -- DANCE-TECH, 3-02 -- In
Seth Riskin's ``Light Dance,'' at the International Dance and
Technology 99 conference in Tempe, movement triggers illumination.
More than 300 participants from 18 nations descended on this sunny,
palm-dotted town, the home of Arizona State University, this year's
conference host. (Jeff Topping/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT16) NEW YORK -- March 02, 1999 -- MUSSORGSKY-OPERA-REVIEW,
3-02 -- Roberto Scandiuzzi in Mussorgsky's ``Khovanshchina,'' at
the Met. Opera is filled with gallant causes and tragic results,
but the political despair of this production elevates it to a
different level of sophistication. (Sara Krulwich/New York Times
Photo)
</P>
<P>
