<P>
   (NYT12) SILVER SPRING, Md. -- March 02, 1999 -- TV-VANZANT-COX,
3-02 -- Iyanla VanZant, a spiritual guru for millions of black
women. She's a regular on TV's ``The Oprah Winfrey Show,'' Hallmark
has turned her daily affirmations into a line of greeting cards,
and her string of best sellers includes ``Acts of Faith,'' a book
many loyal readers call the black women's Bible. ``I used to say I
was just a black woman,'' says Ms. VanZant, who is trying to
broaden her audience beyond her demographic. ``Now I'm a child of
God.'' (Rick McKay/Cox News Service Photo)
