<P>
   (NYT10) SALT FLAT, Texas -- March 02, 1999 --
TRAVEL-TEXAS-3-AZR, 3-02 -- El Capitan and the Gaudalupe Mountains
shine in the distance from the yucca-strewn wastes of Salt Flat.
West Texas is a very empty place. The air is desiccated, the ground
is sandy, the mountains are heated stones, even in October.(Richard
Nilsen/Arizona Republic Photo)
