Harold Nye on the deck of the USS Massachusetts which is undergoing
a $10 million overhaul and then being towed back to its home in
Fall River. Nye, the former seaman apprentice, and the
decommissioned warship with a storied history, will be together
again for what is likely to be the last cruise the ship's World War
II crew members will ever see. (Michael Robinson-Chavez/Boston
Globe Photo)
</P>
