 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   CHARITY-IRS-NYT (moved on Thursday, Feb. 11)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Thursday, Feb. 11,
about a Federal appeals court ruling that upheld the tax-exempt
status of a charity that hired fund-raisers who kept most of the
money they collected referred incompletely to the involvement of a
lawyer, Thomas Troyer. Besides being a nonprofit law specialist at
the firm of Caplan &AMP; Drysdale in Washington, he has been counsel of
record for a group that filed a brief opposing the charity's
position.
</P>
<P>
   The obituary of the director Jose Quintero sent by the New York
Times News Service on Friday, Feb. 26, referred incorrectly to his
birth date. It was Oct. 15, 1924, not Oct. 16, and was the day
before the playwright Eugene O'Neill's 36th birthday, not the day
after his 37th.
</P>
</TEXT>
